Object Oriented Programming (OOPs)
OOPs is just a style of programming. Just a way of writing code that helps us wite large amounts of code eaSILY.
It helps us manage and change large amounts of code.
There are other ways as well as  functional programming and procedural programming.

Pillars of OOPs:

There are four main pillars of OOPs.

1) Inheritance
2) Polymorphism
3) Abstraction
4)Encapsulation
Classes and Objects:
A class is a template/design/map/idea/blueprint from which objects are created.

